Tottenham Hotspur on Saturday confirmed that Gareth Bale has rejoined the club. The 31-year-old, who joins from Real Madrid on a season-long loan, will wear the number 9 shirt. Bale previously wore the number 11 shirt at White Hart Lane. “We are delighted to announce the return of @GarethBale11 to the Club on a season-long loan from Real Madrid!” Tottenham’s official Twitter page tweeted. Bale signed as a 17-year-old from Southampton in 2007. He left for Madrid in a then world-record transfer and returned to North London after seven years. He made 203 appearances for Spurs in all competitions before leaving in 2013, scoring 55 goals.